name: Warm sunlight
description:
Original limited edition signed fine art photograph

I am absolutely fascinated by the timelessness and exquisite details of these specimens. Some were collected over a hundred years ago, and I often find myself dreaming about the adventures of the collectors, their dedication to chart where they found their treasures and leave behind a map of beauty and history. These images were taken whilst volunteering at the School of Botany - Melbourne University Herbarium and are only a tiny sample of the specimens available. Made in a limited edition of 200, each print is personally signed and numbered by me and shipped in sturdy packaging. This photograph is printed by a professional photo lab on archival paper, which has a matte finish and will last a lifetime

DIMENSIONS

Image size

Approx. 20 cm x 30 cm - 8" x 12”

Paper size

Approx. 28 cm x 35 cm - 11" x 14"
This print fits perfectly into a RIBBA Ikea frame.

POSTAGE

Your print will be sent in a protective sleeve and rigid envelope via regular post (Australia) and air mail (International). If you require registered mail or express delivery, please let me know.

ONLY 200 PIECES AVAILABLE

Photography by Heidi Romano at http://www.talesoflight.com.au
